    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nAccording to quickfix.txt\n> Normally the quickfix window is at the bottom of the screen.  If there are\n> vertical splits, it's at the bottom of the rightmost column of windows.\n\nBut actually `:copen` opens a new full width window.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\n:vsplit\n:copen\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nA qf window should be opened at the bottom of the rightmost column of windows\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, vim behaves accordingly documentation\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nOfficial Arch Linux repo",
